msContents.summary: Little is known about Johannes Nicolaus de Milis except that he was the author of this legal text, which he wrote in the 1430s, and that he was probably from Verona. The text itself comprises a legal glossary arranged alphabetically, beginning with "absenti". This manuscript was made in the Bavarian town of Neuberg by the scribe Georgius of Neuberg, who completed the work on Oct. 17, 1458. Although the book was written in Germany by a German scribe, the script and decoration are clearly influenced by the style of Italian manuscripts of the same period.

msItem.colophon: Fol. 344v: "Et sic est finis huius Repertorii scriptum per me Georgiu[m] Newberg[er] de Newberga. Proxima die post diem s[an]cti Galli Anno Millesimo quadringentesimo quinquagesimo octavo."

msItem.title: Repertorium juris civilis
msItem.incipit: Absenti. Queritur actio ex contractu per pr[obar]em celebrato . . . [Fol. 1r]
msItem.explicit: Vxori an debeantur alimenta ab heredibus uiri mortua uira uide sub u[er]bo alimenta que miserocionis. Santio. en constitucio pena vallata ut dicit archi[piscopi]. m c. statute[m] de r[e]p[ara]t li vi in u[er]bo sanctionem. [Fol. 344]
